Continuing political uncertainty in Britain is said to have put off big-name candidates from applying for the position of governor of the Bank of England, 
• Janet Yellen, the former head of the U.S. Federal Reserve, and Raghuram Rajan, a former governor of India’s central bank, were both considered possible candidates for the job.
• But “the Treasury couldn’t get Raghu or Janet to apply,” one unidentified source told the FT.
Lawmakers in the House voted 231-199 yesterday to increase the federal minimum wage to $15 an hour by 2025, 
• “The bill would more than double the federal minimum wage, which is $7.25 an hour — about $15,000 a year for someone working 40 hours a week, or about $10,000 less than the federal poverty level for a family of four.”
• “It has not been raised since 2009, the longest time the country has gone without a minimum-wage increase since it was established 1938.”
